ppropriations of Internet images to using blogs in the classroom to the efforts by universities to claim legal ownership of professors' teaching and research materials. As new technologies and legislation are overturning traditional notions of intellectual property, this volume offers ways to navigate the issues in terms of pedagogy, research, and creating new media texts within the current legal framework.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 4aCommunication : Communication. 4aEducation : Teacher Education. 4aLanguage Arts : Composition and Rhetoric Studies. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Writing / General.2bisacsh1 aBallentine, Brian D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDush, Lisa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGalin, Jeffrey R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHerrington, Tyanna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLee, Sohui, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLogie, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRatliff, Clancy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReyman, Jessica, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRife, Martine Courant, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWestbrook, Steve, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWestbrook, Steve, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143842599340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438425993423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438425993/original  a978-3-11-